<h1 id="interestingelegant-datastructure-and-the-one-im-using-quad-edge-structure-invented-by-guibas-and-stolfi--stores-the-mesh-and-its-dual-and-allows-eleborat-constant-time-traversal">interesting/elegant datastructure, and the one I‚Äôm using, Quad-Edge structure invented by Guibas and Stolfi =&gt; stores the mesh and its dual and allows eleborat constant-time traversal</h1>
<h1 id="original-limitations-2-manifolds">Original limitations: 2-Manifolds</h1>
<h1 id="my-limitations-to-simplify-usage">My limitations (to simplify usage):</h1>
<h1 id="--require-consistent-winding-order--no-non-orientable-surfaces-means-we-dont-have-to-keep-track-about-on-which-side-of-the-surface-we-are-simplifies-lots-of-algorithms-and-later-the-rendering">- require consistent winding-order =&gt; no non-orientable surfaces; means we don‚Äôt have to keep track about on which side of the surface we are; simplifies lots of algorithms and (later) the rendering</h1>
<h1 id="--max-2-faces-may-share-a-vertex-if-they-are-not-connected-through-edges-originating-from-that-vertex-required-for-the-implementation-to-differntiate-the-order-of-edges-around-an-origin">- max. 2 faces may share a vertex, if they are not connected through edges originating from that vertex; required for the implementation, to differntiate the order of edges around an origin</h1>
